&lt;p&gt;At Lyft, our purpose is to serve and connect. We aim to achieve this by cultivating a work environment where all team members belong and have the opportunity to thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lyft Healthcare &amp;amp; Community Access is redefining how risk-bearing provider organizations, health plans, and community organizations think about transportation. We partner with healthcare organizations to solve real access challenges — connecting patients, employees, and communities to the care and resources they need. Our work is meaningful, fast-moving, and high-impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a driven, proactive, and curious Account Manager to join our Strategic Partnerships team. You&#39;ll manage and grow a portfolio of key healthcare partners, serve as a trusted advisor, and play a central role in expanding Lyft&#39;s footprint in one of the most important sectors we serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own relationships across a portfolio of strategic healthcare partners and Home &amp;amp; Community Based Services (HCBS) partners, serving as their primary point of contact and trusted advisor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive quarterly revenue goals by expanding existing partnerships and identifying new business opportunities within identified segments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with engineering and product teams to guide technical integrations, ensuring partners are set up for success and fully leveraging Lyft&#39;s API platform capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of each partner&#39;s business, goals, and challenges — using data to uncover opportunities for growth and operational improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build expertise in healthcare transportation to anticipate partner needs and add strategic value beyond day-to-day account management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with teams across strategy, product, marketing, and legal to deliver for your partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead change management efforts and proactively identify ways to improve processes and drive efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate forecasts and pipeline management in Salesforce CRM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Experience:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in account management, business development, management consulting, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record of exceeding revenue targets in a quota-carrying role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Healthcare industry knowledge, including familiarity with payers, providers, value-based care, and HCBS models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills — comfortable pulling, interpreting, and presenting data to support partner decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills across written, verbal, and presentation formats&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative, team-first mindset with the ability to build relationships across a wide range of stakeholders from business executives to day-to-day operators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter mentality with strong organizational and project management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professionalism and grace under pressure, especially in complex or ambiguous situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Genuine enthusiasm for Lyft&#39;s mission and comfort operating in a fast-paced, evolving environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
