&lt;p&gt;At Lyft, our purpose is to serve and connect. We aim to achieve this by cultivating a work environment where all team members belong and have the opportunity to thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Tech Ops team sits at the intersection of data and ground-level operations. We tackle some of Lyft&#39;s most complex operational challenges — managing the products, services, and compliance workflows that shape the airport experience for drivers, riders, and partners. Our work spans dispatch configuration, regulatory compliance, and cross-functional communications, with our decisions directly affecting driver livelihoods, rider experience, and Lyft&#39;s relationships with airport authorities and regulators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate Program Manager, you&#39;ll own execution of projects and components within larger programs, developing deep subject matter expertise in airport operations and driver products. You&#39;ll work alongside senior managers and cross-functional partners in Engineering, Product, and Business Development — executing with high quality, flagging issues proactively, and continuously improving the processes you own.&lt;/p&gt;
