&lt;li&gt;Airport Products &amp;amp; Driver Experience
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute and maintain airport product configurations (dispatch, queuing, blackouts, rematch) in coordination with senior team members and Engineering partners, following established playbooks and documenting changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support rider-facing product setups including Rider Wayfinding, Static ETA Banners, Reassurance Banners, and Airlines-Terminals configurations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in new feature launches and configuration rollouts, supporting QA testing in staging environments and flagging post-launch issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor program performance using existing dashboards and analytics tools; surface trends and escalate anomalies with appropriate context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Ground Truth Surveys and Client Feedback reviews, identifying and documenting operational issues and improvement opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compliance &amp;amp; Regulatory
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute compliance workflows including XL mode revoking, Queue Education communications, and Placards/Emblems processes following documented SOPs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain geofence configurations using tools like Geofence Reporter and Geohashes, with oversight from senior team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support periodic audits and documentation, escalating issues and ensuring accurate records across assigned program areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Program Execution &amp;amp; Process Improvement
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own execution of assigned projects and workstreams end-to-end, with clear oversight and guidance from senior managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve and automate repetitive processes, documenting improvements for team use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the go-to troubleshooter for your subject area — independently diagnosing issues and escalating with relevant context when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide status updates to stakeholders and cross-functional partners; ask clarifying questions upfront to avoid rework&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
